properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 21 at 9:51PM PST until January 22 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...SNOW WEDNESDAY...

.A warm front will bring snow to the Washington Cascades and
the Northern Blue Mountains on Wednesday. Snow levels will begin
to rise Wednesday night eventually changing precipitation to rain
below 5000 feet.

* WHAT...Moderate snow expected below 3000 feet. Total snow
accumulations of up to 5 inches below 3000 feet around Cle Elum
and Easton. Higher amounts are expected near the Cascade crest
with 8 to 12 inches possible above 3000 feet.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the central Washington Cascades...mainly
in western Kittitas County.

* WHEN...From 7 AM to 10 PM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Precipitation will begin to change over
to rain Wednesday evening as snow levels rise.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM TO 10 PM PST WEDNESDAY BELOW 3000 FEET
